  abstract  = {Using Habermas's theory of communicative action and his remarks on the legitimacy of the state under modern social conditions as a starting point, the author combines normative democratic theory with the critique of ideology. Four necessary-but-not-sufficient conditions of communication for democratic decision making are outlined, including that agreements must be free of ideology. The relation between ideology and democracy is established.},
