  abstract  = {This article revisits Juergen Habermas's long-lasting engagement with the tradition of natural law and argues that his work is unique in the contemporary context because it takes place without seeking to sever all possible connections to natural law. The article reconstructs what Habermas understands by natural law in order to account for its wider relevance as an intellectual resource in modern social theory, and reassesses the natural law elements that still reside in Habermas's own thinking.},
