  RELEVANCE: This 2025 paper captures the most recent institutional developments in the Frankfurt School's own response to postcolonial and decolonial critique, showing that the critique of Habermasian Eurocentrism is now internal to the institution itself. It provides important context for the current state of the debate and suggests that even the heirs of the Frankfurt School recognize the structural Eurocentrism Allen and others have identified.

